      "content": "The field mice analogy is a bit colorful, but I get what you mean about disorganized picking. \n\nThe real issue is the negative variance in the regulators (EC-7782) and the logic gates (EC-5530). They don't seem to be simple miscounts because the physical counts are consistently lower than the system says, even after a double-check. What else could cause these kinds of constant, small losses where items just seem to \"vanish\" without being recorded?",
      "source": "evaluator"
